{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With iOS 5, you can customize the look of your app controls using the new Appearance APIs. The new Appearance Proxy API allows you to efficiently apply a custom appearance to your views and controls, including built-in controls such navigation, tab, and toolbars. These customizations can be applied across your entire app or independently on a per-control basis."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-114-Customizing-the-Appearance-of-UIKit-Controls","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]}]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2011\/114\/","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"}},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Customizing the Appearance of UIKit Controls","roleHeading":"WWDC11","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-114-customizing-the-appearance-of-uikit-controls"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identif